        "text": "τοῦ Θεοῦ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The present is not used instead of the future (Grotius); the subject is here not something future, but what constantly occurs in the life of believers. Augustine suitably says: Charitas ipsa gemit, charitas ipsa orat, contra hanc aures claudere non novit, qui illam dedit.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
