  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This verse is so closely connected with the preceding one, that not more than a comma or semicolon should be placed between them. When a good conscience gives us boldness towards God our prayers are granted, for children in such relations to their heavenly Father cannot ask anything which He will refuse.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And whatsoever we ask",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The ‘and’ is probably epexegetic, as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "1 John 3:20",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 John 3:20",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and explains the special character of our boldness. See on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 John 3:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "we receive of him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The present is to be taken quite literally; not as the present for the future. It may be a long time before we see the results of our prayer; but it is granted at once. As S. Augustine says, ‘He who gave us love cannot close His ears against the groans and prayers of love’.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "because we keep his commandment",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] This should certainly be plural, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "commandments",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": previous English Versions have the plural, and there seems to be no trace of a various reading, so that one suspects a misprint in the edition of 1611. ‘Because’ depends upon ‘receive’, not upon ‘have boldness’: we receive because we are loyal. This is in harmony with the Gospel and with Scripture generally: ‘We know that God heareth not sinners: but if any man be a worshipper of God, and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "do His will, him He heareth",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "’ (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 9:31",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); ‘The Lord is far from the wicked, but He heareth the prayer of the righteous’ (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 15:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 66:18-19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Job 27:8-9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 1:11-15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). For ‘keep His commandments’ see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 John 2:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "do those things which are pleasing in his sight",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Not the same as ‘keeping His commandments’: the one is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "obedience",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which may be slavish, the other is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "love",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". We seem here to have another reminiscence of the Gospel (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 8:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "): ‘Because the things pleasing to Him I always do’. Excepting ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 6:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 12:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the word for ‘pleasing’ occurs nowhere else in N. T. Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 13:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Timothy 2:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
