  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 22.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (as a guarantee that this confidence is not baseless or misdirected) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "whatsoever we ask, we receive from him.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Note the present tense: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "λαμβάνομεν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ληψόμεθα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Whatever the child of God asks as such, he ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "ipso facto",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " obtains (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 15:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). This is the ideal condition of things; for the child of God cannot ask what displeases his Father. And we are his children \"because we keep his commandments.\" The ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ὅτι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " must not be connected too closely with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "λαμβάνομεν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as if our obedience were the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "cause",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of God's hearing our prayers. Our obedience shows that we are such as can pray efficaciously. (For the parallelism, comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 15:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 38:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) 1 John 3:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "We ask (αἰτῶμεν)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "See on Luke 11:9.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "See on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Luke 11:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "We receive of Him (λαμβάνομεν ἀπ' αὐτοῦ)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "On the form of expression, see on 1 John 1:5. For the thought, compare John 15:7.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "On the form of expression, see on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 John 1:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". For the thought, compare ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 15:7",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "We keep (τηροῦμεν)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "See on 1 Peter 1:5. Note the combination of keep and do. Watchful discernment and habitual practice. Compare Psalm 123:2. The same combination occurs 1 John 5:2, 1 John 5:3, where instead of the first τηρῶμεν keep, read ποιῶμεν do.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "See on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Peter 1:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". Note the combination of keep and do. Watchful discernment and habitual practice. Compare ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Psalm 123:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The same combination occurs ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 John 5:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 John 5:3",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", where instead of the first τηρῶμεν keep, read ποιῶμεν do.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Pleasing (ἀρεστά)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "See John 8:29.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "See ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 8:29",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "In His sight (ἐνώπιον αὐτοῦ)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Compare ἕμπροσθεν αὐτοῦ before Him, or in His presence (1 John 3:19). In His sight \"accentuates the thought of the divine regard. Compare John 7:37 and John 20:30\" (Westcott). ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Compare ἕμπροσθεν αὐτοῦ before Him, or in His presence (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 John 3:19",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "). In His sight \"accentuates the thought of the divine regard. Compare ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 7:37",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " and ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 20:30",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "\" (Westcott). ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
